Xj22v7BoIaBub9EM2D9MKYUIoHCmcCsqVkq-6ARjhPmtf13QDOET74hsAGnI-tKEjUcwfwwuTVyg9o5eNmLUD3xAvh1cdLEsxnYNTx-pNXD5zAP8WtY=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering Mockito for tests**\\n\\nI’m thinking about whether generated tests can utilize Mockito. The typical setup might involve JUnit and AssertJ, especially since the old build uses AssertJ. For servlet interfaces, I could bypass server classes and just focus on XML/client methods, but would that provide meaningful coverage? The existing tests already mock server interactions, yet normal usage includes the servlet interfaces. Ultimately, if necessary setup is avoided, it may not lead to meaningful coverage unless certain dependencies are added. I should recommend verifying the dependency for Gradle.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing Gradle and Maven dependencies**\\n\\nI'm exploring if provided dependencies in the Gradle Maven POM are non-transitive. I think about creating a temporary Gradle setup in /tmp and using the installed Gradle version. For simplicity, I could check the Maven dependency tree to understand compile scopes. It seems Maven's provided dependencies aren't transitive to consumers. I might need to verify what’s happening with Gradle when inspecting the native failures—it looks like only two locator tests fail. I might decide to take no action since the existing test scaffold has the necessary dependencies.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating test scaffold dependencies**\\n\\nI'm considering creating tests by copying the current version or generated test scaffold. The existing tests already include a build.gradle with the servlet dependency. The question is whether the library requires setup beyond the typical generated test scaffold for meaningful coverage. If the current setup includes extra dependencies, I think a deterministic setup might be necessary when generating a new version. It seems I don’t need to modify anything or read failure details right now, but I’ll remember to use in-memory construction without needing Docker or additional services.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"Jackrabbit WebDAV exposes servlet-based public APIs and declares javax.servlet only as a provided dependency, so generated tests need an explicit servlet API test dependency to compile and exercise meaningful server/request/response coverage.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"javax.servlet:servlet-api:2.4\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"The artifact's public classes such as AbstractWebdavServlet, DavServletRequest, DavServletResponse, InputContextImpl, OutputContextImpl, and WebdavRequestImpl reference javax.servlet/http types, while jackrabbit-webdav declares servlet-api with provided scope so it is not supplied transitively to tests.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No Docker service or external WebDAV server is required for meaningful coverage. Prefer in-memory XML/property/method tests and lightweight mocks or stubs for HttpServletRequest/HttpServletResponse when exercising servlet-facing APIs. No special environment variables or system properties were found to be required.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The current native-image failure appears to be in existing locator tests rather than missing external setup, so local Gradle and Native Image verification may still require test or metadata fixes after adding the servlet API dependency.\",\n    \"SLF4J has no binding unless tests add one, but this is normally only a logging/no-op warning concern and not required for meaningful coverage.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0ec4cd6cf15bb79e016a423e945f148193ad3433f13bb5cea1\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 4626, "output": 1352, "cacheRead": 25600, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 31578, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782726273656, "responseId": "resp_0ec4cd6cf15bb79e016a423e828a3c8193ba0ed8aa126590af"}, "toolResults": []}
